Executive Profile
Jarrod B. Pontius  Chief Administrative Officer, General Counsel & Corporate Secretary, Convergys CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 1 different industries.45$1,052,021As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Jarrod B. Pontius has been the Chief Administrative Officer and General Counsel of Convergys Corporation since July 1, 2015 and serves as its Company Secretary since September 2012. Mr. Pontius served as Deputy General Counsel of Convergys Corporation since 2012 until July 1,2015. He served as the Chief Legal Officer of Kendle International Inc. since June 2009 and also served as its Vice President and Secretary. In this role, he provided global leadership for all ... legal services, corporate governance and general corporate legal matters for Kendle. Mr. Pontius has more than a decade of experience in both the legal and corporate legal environments. He has a demonstrated track record of success in the areas of corporate law, mergers and acquisitions, corporate development, public company reporting and securities compliance, corporate financing activities and corporate governance. He rejoins Kendle, from General Cable Corporation, a Fortune 500 publicly traded supplier of wire and cable products, where he served as Assistant General Counsel since 2007. Mr. Pontius served as Corporate Counsel and Senior Corporate Counsel for Kendle from 2002 to 2007. His experience also includes serving as an Associate in the business/corporate department of the Cincinnati law firm Frost Brown Todd LLC. Mr. Pontius is a member of both the Cincinnati and Ohio Bar Associations and the Association of Corporate Counsel and is a graduate of the Cincinnati Academy of Leadership for Lawyers. He received his Juris Doctorate from Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland and holds a Bachelor of Science in Finance from Indiana University.Read Full Background




